06/04/2005
BUCHAREST, Romania -- A spokeswoman for the president's office in Bucharest on Tuesday (5 April) denied media reports that three Romanian hostages in Iraq had been released. 
She referred to ongoing operations to free the three journalists but refused to disclose further details. 
The spokeswoman also told reporters that Romanian police had arrested a Syrian-Romanian businessman who claimed to have been contacted by the kidnappers. 
The suspect was close to Muhammad Munaf, an Iraqi-American businessman kidnapped together with the three Romanians. 
(Rompres - 06/04/05; Reuters, AFP - 05/04/05)
